videos.headline: Boston grabs and-1 bucket for South Carolina
videos.description: Aliyah Boston does a great job inside to grab the and-1 bucket as South Carolina leads vs. Arkansas.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Boston grabs and-1 bucket for South Carolina) 2022/3/4 ESHEET

videos.headline: South Carolina's Amihere gets the and-1 score
videos.description: Laeticia Amihere makes a nice effort to get inside for the South Carolina and-1 bucket.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (South Carolina’s Amihere gets the and-1 score) 2022/3/4 ESHEET

videos.headline: Arkansas bench goes wild after Goforth 3-pointer
videos.description: Sasha Goforth had the Arkansas bench going wild after hitting the 3-pointer vs. South Carolina.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Arkansas bench goes wild after Goforth 3-pointer) 2022/3/4 ESHEET

videos.headline: Great ball movement sets up Gamecocks 3
videos.description: Aliyah Boston gets it to Bree Hall for the South Carolina 3-pointer.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Great ball movement sets up Gamecocks 3) 2022/3/4 ESHEET

videos.headline: Boston grabs the bucket down low
videos.description: Laeticia Amihere feeds it to Aliyah Boston down low for the South Carolina bucket.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Boston grabs the bucket down low) 2022/3/4 ESHEET

videos.headline: Staley says Gamecocks survived being 'a little rusty'
videos.description: Dawn Staley tells SEC Now South Carolina had to rely on its defense, which held Arkansas to .313 field-goal shooting, including 5 of 31 (.161) on threes.

videos.headline: Aggressiveness led to Boston's huge game for Gamecocks
videos.description: After piling up 17 points, 14 rebounds, five steals and three blocks in the win over Arkansas, Aliyah Boston says she just played "South Carolina basketball."
